<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Envoy Arrives For Talks With Indian Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jayakody, Sri Lankan minister for Buddhist Sasana, Culture and
Religion Affairs, also came to thank the Indian government for the
moral support New Delhi had extended to Colombo during the counter-
offensive by the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam in northern
Jaffna, the PTI noted.
</P>
<P>
The minister, who is on a three-day visit, will call on Indian
Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee and External Affairs Minister
Jaswant Singh on Wednesday, it added.
</P>
<P>
Carrying a letter from Kumaratunga to Vajpayee, the minister is
accompanied by K. Balapatabendi, secretary to the Sri Lankan
president, and Senake Bandaranayake, Sri Lanka's ambassador to
France.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lankan president proposes to send special envoys
shortly to six other countries, including China, Pakistan, Israel,
the United States and Russia, to thank them for the support
extended to her government to tide over the crisis, the PTI
reported.
</P>
<P>
India decided to extend a 100 million dollar credit facility to
Sri Lanka during Jaswant Singh's recent visit to Colombo, but had
firmly ruled out any military intervention in the island nation.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
