<HEADLINE> Bangladesh, India Sign Agreement to Operate Rail Route </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- An agreement was signed here Tuesday
on operating trains on Benapole-Petrapole route between Bangladesh
and India on the southwestern border, aiming to facilitate
transborder transportation of goods, the United News of Bangladesh
reported.
</P>
<P>
Additional Director General of Bangladesh Railway and
Additional Member of Indian Railway Board Swarup Kumar Gupta
signed the agreement on behalf of their respective side.
</P>
<P>
With the restoration of the rail route after several decades, "
transport of goods between Bangladesh and India would increase
rapidly," said an official announcement.
</P>
<P>
Direct road communication between the two neighboring countries
has already been established with introduction of bus service
between Calcutta and Dhaka in June last year.
</P>
<P>
Negotiations are under way on operating bus service between
Dhaka and Agartala, the capital of northeastern Indian State of
Tripura. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
