<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tropical Depression, Typhoon Kill 2 in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Two people have been killed as
Tropical Depression Edeng and Typhoon Ditang continued to raze the
central and northern Philippines, the Philippine National Disaster
Coordinating Council (NDCC) said Tuesday in a report.
</P>
<P>
The report said a 27-year-old man and a 3-year-old boy were
drown in the flood caused by heavy rains.
</P>
<P>
The NDCC also said more than 400 hundred families in Metro
Manila have moved to different evacuation centers set up by the
government.
</P>
<P>
Most schools in Metro Manila were suspended Tuesday because
some roads were not passable.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Tuesday, Philippine President Estrada ordered
cabinet members to immediately extend the necessary assistance to
flood-hit residents in Metro Manila and nearby provinces.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine Atmospheric, Geophysical and Astronomical
Services Administration said the bad weather will continue in the
next few days and residents in low-lying areas are advised to
remain alert against possible floodings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
