<HEADLINE> Mongolian People's Revolutionary Party Wins Parliament Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The Mongolian People's
Revolutionary Party won in 72 out of the 76 constituencies in the
State Great Khural, or parliament elections held on Sunday, the
central election committee announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 984,709 of the 1,210,441 registered voters cast
their ballots in the election, and the turnout rate reached 81.35
percent, according to the committee.
</P>
<P>
The final result of the election will be presented to President
Nachagyn Bagabandy before July 17.  
</P>
</TEXT>
