injuries. At least two became ill from the heat, one was hit by a
car while bicycling to the race and broke a wrist.
</P>
<P>
In 1993, Charles Tutterow, 40, died of a heart attack he
suffered during the race. The first death occurred a decade ago,
race organizers said. 
