<HEADLINE> E-Trade Grows in Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The Romanian Government intends
to solve as an emergency the issue of e-signature in business
contracts, local weekly Capital said on Wednesday in its latest
issue.
</P>
<P>
Electronic trade is one of the negotiation chapters for Romania
's EU accession which explains the Government's haste to solve
this problem through an emergency ordinance.
</P>
<P>
The draft on e-signature will also be examined by the Justice
Ministry which recommended changing the commercial legislation and
finding schemes to fine-tune the stipulations of the Civil Code
with those of the ordinance.
</P>
<P>
The difficulties related to the creation of the legislation
referring to the development and use of information technologies
will not prevent the Government from meeting the EU recommendation
saying that e-signature in trade contracts should be recognized in
Justice in 2001, sources with the Romanian Ministry of Trade and
Industry said. 
