<HEADLINE> Belgium Issues Arrest Warrant Against Congo Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Belgium Wednesday issued an arrest
warrant against a Congolese government official on charges of
crimes against humanity.
</P>
<P>
The wanted is Congolese Foreign Minister Abdoulaye Yerodia who
was accused by refugees of inciting hatred against them in August
1998 in speeches using such discriminative words as "vermin" and "
extermination
</P>
<P>
The arrest warrant was signed on April 11 by Brussels
Magistrate Damien Vandermeersh but was only issued almost a month
later Wednesday due to legal and technical reasons, according to
legal sources.
</P>
<P>
The arrest warrant was issued in line with a 1993 Belgian law
that demands arrest of those who have committed crimes against
international human rights no matter where they have committed the
crimes and what nationality they are of.
</P>
<P>
The Congolese foreign minister is now liable to arrest if he
enters Belgium or any other country that is willing to execute the
arrest warrant.
</P>
<P>
The Congolese foreign minister will be notified of the Belgian
jurisdiciary decision through diplomatic channels. 
</P>
