<HEADLINE> Peru, Ecuador To Promote Border Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Peru and Ecuador will promote border
trade through a bilateral agreement, said Julian Gamero, director
of bilateral affairs in the Industry, Tourism, Integration, and
International Commerce Negotiations Ministry (MITINCI), here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"The fundamental goal of this agreement will be to promote
industry, agriculture, and agro-industrial activities and the
handicraftsmen of the border zone between the two countries by
means of the organization of fairs and festivals," said Gamero.
</P>
<P>
Gamero said that this region has a very dynamic commercial
activity in spite of the small size of its transactions because it
accumulates an important volume of trading.
</P>
<P>
The government official said that the new agreement will update
the one signed in 1972 because the conditions of the commerce
between the two nations have changed considerably.
</P>
<P>
"The 1972 agreement on fairs was outdated in relation to the
integration advances achieved through the Accord of Cartagena,"
said Gamero.
</P>
<P>
Gamero said that the implementation of each fair or festival
will have to be approved by the MITINCI authorities in the
Peruvian case, and one of the conditions will be the exhibition of
a certificate of origin.
</P>
<P>
"In that way, the agreement will become an agile mechanism that
will permit the active participation of the economic agents of the
region," said Gamero.
</P>
<P>
The MITINCI official said that the agreement involves not only
the fairs, but will include the promotion of cultural exchanges
between the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
