<HEADLINE> Egypt Welcomes Kuwaiti-Saudi Sea Border Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Egypt on Wednesday welcomed the
signing of a maritime border agreement between Kuwait and Saudi
Arabia.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters in the day, Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr
Moussa described the pact as an important achievement that ended a
long-standing dispute.
</P>
<P>
He said that Egypt was relieved to see the two countries finally
clinch the agreement.
</P>
<P>
"The signing of the pact embodies the brotherhood ties that bind
the peoples of Kuwait and Saudi Arabia, and proves that all
problems could be solved through peaceful means in the Arab world,"
Moussa stressed.
</P>
<P>
The two Gulf neighbors signed the agreement on Sunday in Kuwait
to demarcate their maritime borders, which also paved the way for
both sides to delineate with Iran the borders in the northern Gulf,
found to be rich in oil and natural gas resources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
