lasting peace, which he said would be possible through a political
process that produces a settlement meeting aspirations of all
communities, said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lankan government is hoping to bring the constitutional
amendments on devolution of powers before the dissolution of
parliament on August 24 and get it passed, Jayakody told the press
here following the meeting with Singh.
</P>
