<HEADLINE> Timoshinina Wins Platform Diving at European Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Russian Svetlana Timoshinina beat
the same rivals to reclaim the European women's platform diving
title at the European swimming championships on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Timoshinina, who was the winner in Sheffield in 1993, earned a
total of 482.34 points from a combination of the morning's four
semi-final dives and the afternoon's five
final dives on the 10-meter highboard.
</P>
<P>
Germany's Ute Wetzig, the 1989 and 1995 champion, had to settle
for the silver medal with 476.73 points although she led
Timoshinina by 1.59 points going into the last round.
</P>
