<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Anson Chan: China's Entry Into WTO to Benefit HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's Chief Secretary for
Administration Anson Chan said here Wednesday that China's entry
into the World Trade Organization (WTO) will bring benefits to the
Hong Kong business community.
</P>
<P>
"This will benefit not just China. The position where we are,
with our strategic locality, our many decades of doing business
with China, I think our middleman role, far from being undermined
by the mainland's accession to the WTO, will indeed be enhanced,"
Chan said at a luncheon of international chambers of commerce.
</P>
<P>
There will be additional opportunities for both business and
investment, she said.
</P>
<P>
She said that Hong Kong Financial Secretary Donald Tsang is
chairing a committee that is precisely assessing the implications
for Hong Kong as a whole, following China's entry to the WTO.
</P>
<P>
"We have a formal channel of communicating and talking with our
trade counterparts in the mainland," she added. 
</P>
