<HEADLINE> Tai Fook Reports Strong Profit Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Tai Fook Securities Group Limited,
a leading financial services company of Hong Kong, reported a net
profit of 211.2 million HK dollars (27 million U.S. dollars) for
the year ended March 31, 2000.
</P>
<P>
This figure represents an increase of 4.4 times over the
preceding financial year, according to Tai Fook's annual result
report released Wednesday. Total turnover rose 63 percent to 560.3
million HK dollars (71.8 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Peter Wong, group managing director of Tai Fook, attributed the
growth to factors including the opening of more brokerage branches,
launch of online brokerage services in the third quarter of 1999
and the booming local stock market buoyed by the influx of foreign
investments and the demand for Initial Public Offerings in the
telecommunications, technology and Internet sectors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
