<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua Summary of Asia-Pacific Stocks News, July 5 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI -- The Composite Stock Index on the Shanghai Stock
Exchange finished at 1,909.18 points Wednesday, up 1.25 points
from the previous session, according to the Guangfa Securities Co.
Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The SSE-30 index, based on 30 blue chips selected from more
than 400 A shares for domestic investors on the Shanghai Stock
Exchange, closed at 3,882.45 points, up 10.32 points from the
previous session.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
