<HEADLINE> Philippine Military Ready for MILF Attacks: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government said
Wednesday the Armed Forces of the Philippines remain ready to curb
any offensive launched by the Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF),
following reports that the rebel group had threatened to defeat
the military in a protracted war in Mindanao.
</P>
<P>
"If we respond to everything said by the MILF's so-called
spokesman, we'll never get any job done. We have to ignore their
claims," Executive Secretary Ronaldo Zamora said in a radio speech
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A MILF spokesman was earlier quoted as saying that the rebel
group is ready to mount a fullscale war against the government,
even after the military overran most of their strongholds.
</P>
<P>
Zamora stressed the government is pushing for socio-economic
development in Mindanao, instead of a military solution, to
reverse the decades-old official neglect of the south and ring
peace and prosperity to the island.
</P>
<P>
Zamora noted earlier that military operations in Mindanao
against the MILF are "defensive, preemptive and retaliatory."
</P>
</TEXT>
