<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- A judge has been named to
investigate the allegations that Australian sports officials have
helped in the widespread drug use among Olympic athletes.
</P>
<P>
Australian Olympic Committee president John Coates on Wednesday
appointed judge Tricia Kavanagh, a former deputy chairwoman of the
Australian Sports Drug Agency, to probe into claims by Werner
Reiterer, a two-time Olympian and Commonwealth Games discus gold
medalist.
</P>
