<HEADLINE> Securities Analysts Association of China Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The Securities Analysts Association
of China (SAAC) was officially inaugurated here today, marking a
milestone in the development of China's securities analysis
services.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony, vice-chairman of the China
Securities Regulatory Commission Geng Liang said the new SAAC
would help promote rational investment in China's securities
market.
</P>
<P>
Involved in a knowledge-intensive profession, securities
analysts have been a relatively young and small group in China,
which reintroduced its stock market a decade ago.
</P>
<P>
According to Geng, China now has about 1,500 licensed
securities analysts and 115 licensed securities advisory companies.
</P>
<P>
Lin Yixiang, Vice-President of the China Securities Co., Ltd.
and SAAC's first elected chairman, said the organization would
advocate self-discipline in the industry, promote exchanges with
international counterparts, organize training for members to
improve their ethical and professional standards and protect their
interests.
</P>
<P>
Today's conference also passed the association's constitution
and ethical standards for securities analysts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
