<HEADLINE> Company of HK Garrison Cited (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The company originated in a Communist Party of China-led Red
Army company known for its brave crossing of the Dadu River during
the Long March in the mid-1930s to break a siege by Kuomintang
troops.
</P>
<P>
Since July 1, 1997, when the PLA garrison took over barracks in
Hong Kong after the home-coming of the territory, the company has
fulfilled its duty in defending Hong Kong, and its officers and
men have been widely praised by local residents for their
meritorious deeds and good image.
</P>
<P>
In his address, Yu spoke highly of the company's contribution
to the prosperity and stability of Hong Kong. The company is a
symbol of the determined will of the garrison troops to carry out
and safeguard the principle of "one country, two systems" and do
their utmost for the great cause of the reunification of the
motherland, he said.
</P>
