<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unified Language Important to National Unity: Legislators </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The adoption of the rule of law
regarding the promotion and popularization of the common language
is of great importance for safeguarding national unity,
strengthening solidarity between people of different ethnic groups
and boosting social and economic development.
</P>
<P>
This was a call made by members of the Standing Committee of
the National People's Congress (NPC) at a meeting today to discuss
a draft of the law on the national common language. The lawmakers
reached a consensus on the promulgation of such a law.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, attended the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
In the course of the discussion, the legislators showed their
concern over widespread errors in the use of Putonghua, or
standard Chinese, especially in advertisements and other business
activities.
</P>
<P>
Fearing that such errors may have a negative effect on young
people, they proposed that the teaching of Putonghua and standard
characters be compulsory in all schools.
</P>
<P>
Since the Chinese language is also used in Taiwan, Hong Kong,
Macao and Singapore, as well as other parts of the world where
overseas Chinese live, the State Language Working Committee under
the Ministry of Education should make efforts to spread Chinese
worldwide, according to the legislators.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, some of the speakers suggested that overseas
Chinese be consulted before publishing any new simplified
characters to avoid misunderstandings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000705.0131 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Hold Festival of Delicacies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Starting this year, China will
hold an annual festival of delicacies, organizers announced here
today.
</P>
<P>
The first such festival will take place from November 1 to 8 in
this capital of east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The festival is jointly sponsored by the State Administration
of Internal Trade and the municipal people's government of
Hangzhou.
</P>
<P>
During the festival, delicacies from all parts of the country,
along with over 200 local snacks, will be available in the city's
hotels and restaurants.
</P>
<P>
The best 10 chefs in the nation will be selected, and medals be
awarded for the best cuisine and snacks, the organizers said.
</P>
</TEXT>
