<HEADLINE> Intense Heat Wave Hits Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Turkey has come under the spell of a
heat wave Wednesday, with temperatures soaring above 40 degrees
centigrade in the country's west.
</P>
<P>
The intense heat wave had been predicted by the State
Meteorology Office, which warned the upsurge would reach its height
in Turkey on July 5-6, raising temperatures to 40 degrees in the
Marmara region and 43 degrees in the Mediterranean and the Aegean
regions.
</P>
<P>
The expected temperatures in Central Anatolia and the Black Sea
region would be below 40 degrees.
</P>
<P>
Meteorology experts say that the sizzling hot weather will
continue to be in effect for a few days, and warn people against
direct exposure under the scorching sun.
</P>
<P>
They also advise people not to allow kids, elderly and heart-
troubled people out if not necessary.
</P>
<P>
Turkey's school year ends in June and it is fortunate that all
students are now on summer vocation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
