Lebanon due to its weak excuses and such a move could not help
maintain the peace along the border," Sneh told the Israel Radio.
</P>
<P>
Sneh also warned the Lebanese government not to let the local
military group such as Hezbollah to resume military activities
against Israel in south Lebanon, saying any anti-Israel activities
will be met with harsh retaliation.
</P>
<P>
A potentially dangerous vacuum has been created in south Lebanon
due to the delay in full implementation of U.N. Security Council
resolution 425, foreign diplomats here have said.
</P>
<P>
The lingering uncertainty over the international boundary and
absence of a full U.N. peacekeeping force in south Lebanon since
Israel's troops withdrawal on May 24, mean a flare-up of violence
is still possible, the diplomats added.
</P>
<P>
Special U.N. Middle East envoy Terje Roed Larsen and other U.N.
experts are due to arrive here Wednesday evening in an effort to
resolve the problems concerning the border line.
</P>
<P>
Larsen reported to the Security Council on Monday about the
delineation of the border between Israel and Lebanon, saying 12
points along the border need modification.
</P>
<P>
Most of these disputed points were reported to be relatively
minor, where Israeli patrol routes, installations or equipment
encroached on Lebanese territory. The only major problem was
reported to be north of border town of Metulla, where Israel
Defense Forces were said to have been seen in trenches on land
considered to be inside Lebanon. 
</P>
