<P>
SHANTOU, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Police in Shantou, south China's
Guangdong Province, are holding two men and a woman suspected of
kidnapping a Hong Kong businessman and taking him from Shenzhen to
Chaoyang, both in Guangdong.
</P>
<P>
According to police, the Hong Kong businessman was kidnapped on
June 8, when 38-year-old Huang Zhaolin and an unnamed party broke
into his residence in Shenzhen and took him to Chaoyang.
</P>
<P>
After beating and torturing the businessman, the kidnappers
demanded that a ransom of one million Hong Kong dollars be
transferred into two bank accounts in Hong Kong.
</P>
