BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The China Insurance Regulatory
Commission (CIRC) today announced it has penalized four insurance
company branches for irregularities in automobile insurance
business.
</P>
<P>
The penalties faced by the China Ping An Insurance Company's
branches in Nanjing and Tianjin cities, the China Pacific
Insurance Company's branch in Nanjing, and a Yunnan provincial
branch of the People's Insurance Company of China involve a three-
month suspension of their automobile insurance business.
</P>
<P>
The companies were charged with mismanagement, paying illegal
commissions and discrepancies in financial management, the CIRC
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
