<HEADLINE> China to Host Int'l Horn Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- China will host the 32nd
International Horn Society (IHS) Symposium and 2000 Beijing
International Horn Festival from July 22 to 28 at Beijing's
Century Theater.
</P>
<P>
Century Performance Corporation announced here today that more
than 250 overseas horn soloists and 500 Chinese musicians will
participate in the musical event, sponsored by the Chinese
Musician's Association (CMA) and the China International Youth
Exchange Center.
</P>
<P>
The symposium and festival will include lectures given by world
horn masters, academic workshops, a horn exhibition, a contest and
17 concerts, the organizers said.
</P>
<P>
Chinese audiences will have opportunities to enjoy performances
from world-famous horn players Froydis Ree Wekre, Peter Kurau and
Hans Pizka.
</P>
<P>
The performance schedule of 17 concerts include most of
classical horn pieces composed by Mozart, Beethoven, Wagner and
other masters.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1969, the IHS links people who have common
interest in horn and playing horn. The society, with over 3,000
members, organizes a symposium in each year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
