<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Rise 1.47 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks closed up 1.47
percent, or 238.51 points, at 16,474.276 on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the market rallied on Wednesday as reports that
conglomerate Hutchison Whampoa Ltd. was due to sell a 35-percent
stake in its British mobile phone joint venture sparked a buying
spree in telecom counters.
</P>
<P>
Select individual stocks dominated trade. Among the winners
were Cathay Pacific, TVB and some China-linked red chips on a
string of bullish corporate news.
</P>
<P>
Of the four sub-indices of the benchmark Hang Seng Index (HSI),
only Utilities dropped 0.46 percent while Finance, Properties and
Industry &AMP; Commerce rose by 1.08 percent, 1.21 percent and 1.89
percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The turnover on Wednesday was 12.861 billion HK dollars (1.649
billion U.S. dollars), 46.98 percent up from the volume on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
China-related stocks ended mixed with the Hang Seng China
Enterprises Index down 0.17 percent and the Hang Seng China-
Affiliated Corp Index up 3.09 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng IT Index gained 0.6 percent and the Hang Seng IT
Portfolio Index increased by 0.57 percent.
</P>
<P>
The HSI opened up 39.57 points, or 0.24 percent, at 16,131.77
Wednesday and closed the morning session at 16,417.58. 
</P>
