<HEADLINE> Turkey Gives Visa-Free Access to Macao SAR Passport Holders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Beginning on Wednesday Turkey grants
visa-free access to holders of the passport of China's Macao
Special Administrative Region (SAR), according to sources with the
Identification Services of the Macao SAR government.
</P>
<P>
Following Singapore, the Republic of Korea and the Philippines,
Turkey is the fourth country to give visa-free access to Macao SAR
passport holders since the founding of the SAR last December.
</P>
<P>
Holders of the Macao SAR passport can stay in Turkey for up to
20 days each time.
</P>
<P>
The Macao SAR government gave visa-free treatment to Turkish
passport holders on May 2 this year and they can stay in Macao for
up to 20 days.
</P>
<P>
So far, a total of 41 countries have recognized the passport of
the Macao SAR.  
</P>
</TEXT>
