<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close Firmer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The resurgent telecommunication
and technology sectors continued their strong performance
Wednesday, leading the Australian stock market to a higher close.
</P>
<P>
The All Ordinaries Index finished 12 points higher to 3,271.5.
</P>
<P>
The strength was with the industrial stocks. The All
Industrials Index ended 33.7 points higher at 5,743.8 while the
All Resources Index sank 13.2 points to reach 1,296.4.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 1.004 billion shares worth 1.771 billion
Australian dollars (1.063 billion U.S. dollars). There were 966
rising and 594 falling stocks while 413 others were steady.
</P>
<P>
The banks were also indecisive, National Australia dipped 33.8
cents to 25.78 Australian dollars, ANZ lost 1.8 cents to 12.45
Australian dollars, the Commonwealth gained 13 cents to 27.6
Australian dollars and Westpac picked up 3.1 cents to 11.901
Australian dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
