<HEADLINE> Another Quake Jolts Bengkulu, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.2 on the
Richter scale jolted Indonesia's Bengkulu and its environs early
Wednesday morning, according to the Antara News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted a source at the local geophysics station as
saying the epicenter of the quake was located 248 kilometers
southwest of Manna town, South Bengkulu, and 33 kilometers beneath
sea level.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of casualties and material
losses caused by the quake.
</P>
<P>
An earthquake measuring 7.3 on the Richter scale hit Bengkulu
on June 4. At least 130 persons were killed and hundreds of others
injured in the quake which also devastated thousands of buildings.
</P>
<P>
Since the June 4 quake, the local geophysics station has
recorded more than 2,000 aftershocks of different intensities.
</P>
