<HEADLINE> France nearly Ends Brazil's Reign at the Top of FIFA Rankings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 5 (Xinhua) -- European Champions France nearly
ended Brazil's reign at the top of FIFA's world rankings published
on Wednesday, as Italy and Portugal also made significent climbs.
</P>
<P>
Brazil totalled 825 points and France finished second with 808
points.
</P>
<P>
Lagging 70 points behind only a month ago, France nearly
polevaulted to the top with their dramatic extra-time Golden Goal
win over Italy in Euro 2000's final last Sunday at Rotterdam,
Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
The Czech Republic remain in third with 753 points while Euro
quarter-finalist's Spain hold joint fourth with surging Argentina,
who are unbeaten in South American World Cup qualifiers.
</P>
<P>
Losing finalist's Italy moved up eight places to sixth while
the surprising Portuguese also moved up eight places to seventh
with their semi-final appearance at Euro.
</P>
<P>
England have slumped to 15th after losing to Portugal and
Romania in the Euro group stages prompting a drop of three places.
</P>
<P>
Euro co-hosts Netherlands moved up 13 places to eighth after
reaching the semi-finals.  
</P>
