<HEADLINE> Chinese, Oman Senior Military Officers on Bilateral Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian said that furthering the relations between China and Oman
conforms to the fundamental interests of the people of the two
countries, and benefits world peace, stability and development.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission and
a State Councilor, made the remarks here today while meeting with
visiting Khamis Al-Kalbani, chief of staff of the Oman armed
forces.
</P>
<P>
He said that Chinese and Oman people have enjoyed a long
friendship, and as they share similar histories, China and Oman
now are facing the common task of developing the economy and
creating opportunities for cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China values the ties with Oman and is ready to
develop a long-term, stable and multi-level cooperation with Oman
in all fields.
</P>
<P>
Chi expressed the gratitude for the support of the Oman
government towards the Chinese on the Taiwan issue, and voiced his
hope to further the existing friendly relations between the two
countries and their armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Chi also expounded on the Chinese government's view on the
international situation, China's foreign policy and the principled
stance on the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
Al-Kalbani said that Oman and China have shared identical or
similar stand towards international affairs, and the relations of
the two countries have developed rapidly since they forged
diplomatic ties in 1978.
</P>
<P>
He added that the Oman government and armed forces would like
to promote cooperation with the Chinese side. He reaffirmed that
Oman supports the One-China policy.  
</P>
