HONG KONG, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The gold price in Hong Kong went
down six HK dollars to close at 2,664 HK dollars a tael Wednesday,
according to Po Sang Bank, one of the major gold dealers in Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
The gold price is equivalent to 287.08 U.S. dollars a troy
ounce, down 0.67 U.S. dollars from the previous trading session at
Wednesday's exchange rate of one U.S. dollar against 7.7895 HK
dollars. 
</P>
