<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Firmer on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Share prices eked out a modest
gain on the Singapore Stock Market Wednesday, lifted by buying of
penny stocks and selected blue chips.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) gained 7.91 points to
end at 2,080.33.
</P>
<P>
The total volume increased to 620.09 million units worth 646.85
million Singapore dollars (about 372.46 million U.S. dollars).
Advancing issues overwhelmed decliners by 210 to 117 with 264
counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Ionics topped the volume list registering a turnover of 37.31
million units. FDS Netw was the second most-heavily traded stock
as it had 32.05 million shares done. Achieva was the next with 30.
14 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
SPH 100 was the top gainer of the day, rising by 80 cents to
close at 28 Singapore dollars. Both SIA and SIA 200 finished the
day at 17.9 Singapore dollars, up 40 cents. CSA and CityDev picked
up 30 cents to end at 6.8 and 9.65 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
PacCent was the biggest loser of the day, plummeting by 150
cents to close at 21.9 Singapore dollars. Chartered and SPH as
well as Datacrft shed 20 cents each to finish at 15.7 and 27.3
Singapore dollars and 8.55 U.S. dollars respectively. OUE drifted
down by 16 cents to end at 4.16 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said recent listings and penny stocks have dominated
trading so far this week and most retail and institutional
investors continued to glue to the sidelines, noting that IPO
debutante FDS Network Group accounted for 5 percent of the total
volume.
</P>
<P>
They said proprietary traders have been the main players over
the past days and the action pattern of centering around the small
cap counters looked likely to continue.  
</P>
</TEXT>
