<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai, HK Attract Each Other </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This is a new strategy of Hong Kong to attract Shanghai
citizens to the region.
</P>
<P>
More and more Shanghai citizens visited Hong Kong after it was
returned to the motherland in 1997. At the same time, Hong Kong
people's interest in ever-changing Shanghai is also growing.
</P>
<P>
In the first five months of the year, the number of Shanghai
tourists to Hong Kong increased by 56 percent. Some 68,000 Hong
Kong people traveled to Shanghai, more than the figure for the
corresponding period last year, according to statistics released
by the HKTA Shanghai office.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's new tourism attractions include the Orient Pearl
Tower and the International Conference Center. And its traditional
places of interest are Yu Park and the Jade Buddha Temple.
</P>
<P>
The rural areas outside Shanghai, Chongming Island, as well as
the ancient town of Zhujiajiao and rivers in the vicinity of the
city were also appealing to Hong Kong citizens.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai residents most often head for Hong Kong's Ocean Park,
Victoria Port, the former residence of late Taiwan popular music
star Teng Li-chun, watch dragon boat races, or go shopping.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, Shanghai tourist arrivals in
Hong Kong surpassed 15,000, a jump of 31 percent over the same
period last year. The majority of the people went to Hong Kong on
a three-person family tour package.
</P>
<P>
Travel agencies predicted that people from Shanghai and
neighboring Zhejiang Province will visit Hong Kong in large
numbers this summer.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong Tourism Association, in cooperation with China
International Travel Service (CITS), will encourage Shanghai
students to travel to Hong Kong in groups and visit science,
culture and space centers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000705.0195 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Host International Exhibition on Housing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The 2000 China International
Exhibition on Housing, sponsored by China's Ministry of
Construction, is scheduled to be held between July 12-16.
</P>
<P>
Some 300 real estate enterprises and household product
producers from Canada, the United States, Denmark, Austria, China
and other countries and regions are expected to display their
latest technologies and goods at the show.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will be divided into six parts, displaying the
evolution of comfortable housing in China, real estate firms, new
technologies and products from abroad, China's quality household
products and housing development in various Chinese cities.
</P>
<P>
According to Nie Meisheng, director of the Housing
Industrialization Promotion Center under the Ministry of
Construction, China is in the midst of a massive housing
construction drive, building more than 400 million square meters
of floor space annually with investment exceeding 400 billion yuan
(about 48 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Massive housing construction and increasing sales have spurred
China's economic development, and have become a major focus of
consumer spending, the official said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
