<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese T-bond Up on Wednesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Chinese T-bond trade rallied
broadly on Wednesday, but with thinner trading.
</P>
<P>
The trading volume on the market totaled 1.09 billion yuan,
down 501 million yuan in comparison with the already sluggish
trade on Tuesday, according to Homeway, China's leading on-line
financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Bond 009704 (10-year bond with a rate of 9.78 percent),
recouped some losses with a jump of 0.32 percent, pressing the
yield down to 4.00 percent. Bond 009908 (10-year bond with a rate
of 3.30 percent) also saw a firm rise of 0.35 percent to 101.39
yuan, with yield down 0.05 percentage point to 3.49 percent.
</P>
<P>
Bond 010004, the only bond with floating interest rate on the
market, gained 0.17 percent to close at 101.74 yuan with a yield
of 2.67 percent. It is still the most active with the biggest
turnover of 411 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The shrinking turnover on the T-bond market indicated that most
would-be investors are still cautiously watching and waiting. But
as market insiders expect the domestic stock market to fluctuate
downwards and drive some conservative investors into fixed-income
government securities market in the near future, bonds may turn
upbeat in the weakness of domestic shares, Homeway analysts said.
</P>
<P>
China's repo market was quiet today, with trading volume on the
three-day, seven-day, 14-day, and 28-day transactions shrank from
5.87 billion yuan on Tuesday to 2.01 billion yuan today. Meanwhile,
the interest rate on the three-day transaction dropped by 6.2
percentage points to 3.8 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
