<HEADLINE> China's Fund Market Corrects Slightly on Wednesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- China's fund market corrected
slightly Wednesday, with 4 funds rising, 6 unchanged and 16
declining.
</P>
<P>
Among the 22 funds that were in discounted trading, most
changed within 0.01 yuan from the last close. Fund Taihe, which
announced the interim divident allocation plan, still gained the
most attention and continued to go upwards, according to Homeway,
China's leading on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
This reflects that market investors pay attention to the cash
return of funds, Homeway analysts said.
</P>
<P>
The other 4 restructured funds dropped between 4 percent and 7.
5 percent, following strong rises in the previous days. Market
experts said that it was because the speculation in the old fund
market was brought into the new fund market, according to Homeway.
</P>
</TEXT>
