<HEADLINE> Afghan Taliban Keen on Prisoners Swap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Spokesman for Afghanistan's
ruling Taliban Maulvi Abdul Hai Mutmain said Wednesday that the
militia has great interest in exchanging prisoners with the
opposition and is making all-out efforts in this regard.
</P>
<P>
Talking to the media in Kandahar, South Afghanistan, he said
delegations from both sides had met the prisoners of war and they
exchanged lists of prisoners as well, according to the Associated
Press of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Prior to recent fighting between the Taliban and the opposition,
the two factions had exchanged delegations in preparation for a
prisoners swap.
</P>
<P>
The delegations were satisfied after meeting the prisoners,
Mutmain said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the opponents were also satisfied to see that
their prisoners are safe and sound and in good health.
</P>
<P>
Having controlled over 80 percent of Afghanistan, the Taliban
are combating the north-based opposition to rule the whole country.
</P>
</TEXT>
