<HEADLINE> Shenzhen A-share Market Edges Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen composite index closed
at 596.2 points on Wednesday, down 0.51 points from the last close.
The sub-index closed at 4735.26 points, 18.22 points lower than
that of yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The turnover hit 8.81 billion yuan (1.06 billion U.S. dollars),
8.23 percent less than yesterday's 9.6 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen composite index dipped slightly today with thin
trading. Hi-tech stocks performed actively, according to Homeway,
China's leading on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
However, investors were concerned about IPO (Initial Public
Offering) pressure. Four new shares will be listed and two new
companies will issue on-line on the country's two bourses in
Shanghai and Shenzhen tomorrow, Homeway analysts said.
</P>
<P>
Shandong Shantui Construction Machinery Co., Ltd. was the top
gainer today with price up 9.9 percent to 15.21 yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
Neimonggu Hongfeng Industry Co., Ltd. was the biggest loser
today. Its price dropped 10.01 percent to 15.19 yuan per share,
hit by selling pressure.
</P>
<P>
The market is likely to move below 600 points tomorrow, as the
IPO market will drain more money from the secondary market,
Homeway analysts predicted.  
</P>
