<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenzhen B-share Market Down at Wednesday Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen B-share market index
dipped 0.76 points or 0.68 percent to close at 111.15 points at
Wednesday close, extending losses in the last hour of trading.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover was 65.48 million HK dollars, up 14.05
million dollars or 27.32 percent from Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The market disregarded a series of positive news, which should
support the idea that China will speed up reforms of the stock
market as the country prepares to join the World Trade
Organization, according to Homeway, China's leading on-line
financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
China will encourage foreign companies to list on its domestic
bourses, the domestic media quoted assistant foreign trade
minister Ma Xiuhong as saying yesterday. Qualified candidates can
seek listing either on the yuan-denominated A-share market or the
foreign currency B-share market, the first official confirmation
since British consumer goods maker Uniliver Plc filed its
application for a listing on China's A-share market last Friday.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, China's securities regulator is considering a
proposal to let companies that have already listed H shares in
Hong Kong to sell yuan-denominated A shares in the country. The
China Securities Regulatory Commission may pick some H share
companies as "trial cases" to conduct the experiment, Homeway said.
</P>
<P>
Rising shares lagged behind falling ones by 12 to 37, with 5
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Changyu rose 4.66 percent to 3.37 HK dollars, while Chiwan Base
added 4.08 percent to 2.55 HK dollars
</P>
<P>
ST Lionda dropped 4.90 percent to 1.36 HK dollars, while Huafa
Elect shed 4.88 percent to 1.95 HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
The market is likely to continue to oscillate, hovering around
the current level and with cautious sentiment lingering on,
Homeway analysts predicted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
