<HEADLINE> Kenya Appeals for Food Aid Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi
has appealed once again to the international community to assist
Kenyans in combating famine.
</P>
<P>
"Kenya has never experienced drought and famine of this
magnitude," Moi was quoted as saying by the newspaper Daily Nation
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The drought was threatening the lives of millions all over the
continent, he said when speaking during celebrations to mark the
224th anniversary of American independence at the residence of
U.S. Ambassador to Kenya Johnnie Carson in Muthaiga, Nairobi.
</P>
<P>
The president thanked the United States for responding
"generously to supplement the (Kenyan) government's efforts".
However, he did not divulge how much the Americans have donated.
</P>
<P>
On June 7, Moi made an emotional appeal for an immediate 11.5
billion shillings (about 15.3 million U.S. dollars) donation for
starving Kenyans.
</P>
<P>
The World Food Program said Tuesday that accelerated food aid
for 3.3 million Kenyans was urgently needed.
</P>
<P>
So far, Kenya has received indications from donors to provide
25 to 30 percent of the food aid which it requested. 
</P>
</TEXT>
