<DOCNO> XIE20000705.0243 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Cuts Prices for Some Medicine by Big Margin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- China's pricing authorities have
decided to cut the retail prices for some medicine by an average
of 30 percent as of July 10.
</P>
<P>
The price cuts cover nine categories of 57 specifications,
including interferon and some other antibiotics, according to a
news release issued today by the State Development Planning
Commission (SDPC).
</P>
<P>
"New prices will save consumers 800 million yuan of medical
fees annually," a SDPC official said, adding that the effort will
also facilitate the government-initiated medical care reform in
cities.
</P>
<P>
The official attributed the price cuts mainly to lowered prices
of raw-material-based medicines, lowered costs due to production
expansion, and fierce market competition.
</P>
<P>
The SDPC also will take more steps to narrow the space for
kickbacks in medicine sales.  
</P>
</TEXT>
