<HEADLINE> Wei Jianxing on Transparency of Grassroots Gvt Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 5 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese party leader has urged
town and township officials to increase transparency of government
work and promote democracy, so as to boost rural reform and
stability.
</P>
<P>
Wei Jianxing, Standing Committee member of the Political Bureau
of the Communist Party Central Committee, made the remark during
his study tour in Tianjin, 100 km east of Beijing, from July 2-4.
</P>
<P>
Wei, who is mainly responsible for the Party's disciplinary
issues, visited Baodi County, Tianjin, and talked with local
officials and ordinary people on promoting grassroots democracy
and openness of government work.
</P>
<P>
Highlighting the importance of the issue, Wei urged all
localities nationwide to participate in the effort.
</P>
<P>
The transparency plan should be combined with the strengthening
of internal supervision and management, so that any officials who
attempt to sidestep the rules with illegal activities will be
discovered, he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted the trickle-down effect of the work, saying that
boosting transparency of grassroots government work can lead to
the improvement of village level operations. 
</P>
