<HEADLINE> Weather Not to Affect College Entrance Exams </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Weather conditions in most parts of
China will be favorable from July 7-9 when the national college
entrance exam is held.
</P>
<P>
Some 3.8 million students are scheduled to take part the exam,
that boasts the largest number of examinees in the world.
</P>
<P>
According to the China's Central Meteorological Station,
southern China will not see heavy rainfall or high temperatures
that could affect local transportation systems, though
intermittent rainfall is forecast for some parts in the area.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, northern and northeast China and the Yellow River
and Huai River valleys will experience clouds and rain, with the
highest temperature expected to be 35 degrees Celsius.
</P>
<P>
Clear weather conditions will dominate northwest China during
the period, with temperatures ranging from 34-37 degrees,
meteorologists said.  
</P>
