<HEADLINE> English-language Police Hotline Opens in Nanjing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The new English emergency police
number "110" in Nanjing, capital of east China's Jiangsu Province,
rang for the first time in the wee hours of July 1.
</P>
<P>
Two Iranian sailors dialed 110 to report a dispute over the
price of the wine they drank with a Chinese teahouse owner. The
officer stationed at the 110 switchboard answered the call in
English, local police arrived at the scene within four minutes,
and the problem was resolved.
</P>
<P>
Nanjing, Wuxi and Suzhou in this prosperous province launched
the 110 English service on July 1 to provide better service for
ever-increasing population of foreign investors and tourists in
the cities.  
</P>
