<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Calls for Perfecting "Shanghai Five" Mechanism at Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DUSHANBE, Tajikistan, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President
Jiang Zemin called here on Wednesday for fleshing out and
perfecting the "Shanghai Five" mechanism and deepening cooperation
among China, Tajikistan, Russia, Kazakhstan and Kyrgyzstan in
security, trade and other international arenas.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the call at an annual summit meeting of the heads of
state of the five nations. The annual event, commonly known as the
"Shanghai Five" summit, was started in Shanghai, China, in April
1996, when the top leaders of the five countries held their first
summit to exchange views on bilateral and multilateral cooperation
and other regional and international issues on common interest.
</P>
<P>
Also attending the Dushanbe summit are hosting Tajik President
Emomali Rakhmonov, Russian President Vladimir Putin, Kazakh
President Nursultan Nazarbayev, and Kyrgyz President Askar Akayev.
Uzbek President Islam Karimov is present at this year's summit for
the first time as an observer.
</P>
<P>
In his speech at the summit, which was presided over by Tajik
President Rakhmonov, Jiang Zemin put forward a four-point proposal
for fleshing out and perfecting the "Shanghai Five" mechanism,
deepening the five-nation cooperation in national and regional
security and stability, expanding bilateral and multilateral
economic and trade cooperation, and strengthening coordination
among the five nations in the international arenas.
</P>
<P>
He said that with the annual summit of the heads of state of
the five countries as the center-piece and a driving force,
meetings of the relevant government departments of the five
countries should be promoted so as to push forward specific
cooperation projects among them in every possible field, thus help
shaping a multi-level, multi-area consulting mechanism within the
"Shanghai Five" framework, and in due course, help developing the
present five-nation meeting mechanism into a five-nation
cooperation mechanism.
</P>
<P>
On upgrading the five-nation cooperation on national and
regional security, Jiang called for joint actions of the five
countries to crack down on all forms of extremist forces,
separatist forces and terrorist forces in the region.
</P>
<P>
"We cannot overlook the disrupting and sabotaging factors
coming from within and outside of the five-nation region that are
threatening peace and stability of the region," Jiang said against
the background that all the five countries want an environment of
long-term peace and stability to concentrate on national economic
buildup in the face of the world trend of economic globalization.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president also urged the five countries to create
necessary conditions, bring into full play their respective
advantages, expand mutual investment, and explore different ways
of economic and technological cooperation, so as to push forward
their overall bilateral and multilateral economic and trade
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
In this regard, he welcomed the other four nations to actively
participate in China's national undertaking of developing the
western part of the country.
</P>
<P>
In the field of international affairs, Jiang stressed the
importance of strengthened cooperation among the five countries in
maintaining the authority of the United Nations, particularly that
of the U.N. Security Council, and in upholding such principles in
international relations as respecting national sovereignty, and
non-interference in other country's internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
He suggested that the five nations strengthen their
coordination of positions in opposing hegemony and power politics
in world affairs, and in the joint efforts to promote the multi-
polarization process of the world politics.
</P>
<P>
Describing the "Shanghai Five" mechanism as "a historic outcome
" of today's world development in the conclusion of his speech,
Jiang called on statesmen and politicians of the five nations to
demonstrate their sense of responsibility and sense of mission to
work for the world's multi-polarization process, for the
establishment of a just and rational new order in the world
politics and economic development, and for peace and stability of
the world.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president arrived here on Monday on a two-day state
visit to Tajikistan before attending the summit meeting of the "
Shanghai Five." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000705.0273 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
