<HEADLINE> Urban 21 Conference held in Berlin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, July 4 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan
here Tuesday urged more efforts to turn cities into places where
everybody feels safe and worthy.
</P>
<P>
At the opening of a global conference on the urban future in
the 21st century, he said while cities are engines of growth and
incubators of civilization, they at the same time can be places of
disease, violent crime, unemployment and poverty.
</P>
<P>
In his address "The future of mankind lies in the cities," he
said within 25 years the number of city dwellers in the world
will grow to two-thirds from the nearly half at present, and that
most of growth will be in the developing countries.
</P>
<P>
"We have entered the urban millennium," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Some 3,500 representatives from more than 100 countries and
regions are attending the three-day world conference, which will
focus on issues such as problems urbanization has brought to both
developed and developing countries and how to deal with them.
</P>
<P>
Germany's Chancellor Gerhad Schroeder said at the opening that
one of the serious issues mankind is facing is how to keep cities
developing smoothly.
</P>
<P>
A report, drafted by a special committee and presented to the
conference, predicted the global trend of urbanization and made
recommendations for dealing with them.
</P>
<P>
The conference is expected to adopt a statement before it
closes on Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
