ANKARA -- Turkey is eyeing for the 300 million U.S. dollars
third tranche of a 4-billion-dollar stand-by loan that was
endorsed by the IMF at the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
The IMF approval is expected to further ease Turkey's
international borrowing. The Treasury plans to launch a euro-
dominated bond issue this month. (Turkey-IMF) 
