<DOCNO> XIE20000705.0298 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Experts Doubt Russian Find of Pyramids in Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Chinese experts expressed their
suspicion over Russian's finding of pyramids on Kangrinboqe
Mountain in Tibet, China Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
The English-language daily quoted the experts as saying that
the Russians may have mistaken mountains shaped like pyramids to
be pyramids.
</P>
<P>
A group of Russian scientists claimed that they had found more
than 100 pyramids and many cultural relics last year on Tibet's 6,
656-metre-high Kangrinboqe, the highest peak in the Gangdise Range.
</P>
<P>
Yang Yichou, a geographer with the Institute of Geography under
the Chinese Academy of Sciences, attributed the pyramid-like
appearance of these mountains to the combined efforts of the
geological movements and wind erosion.
</P>
<P>
The Russian scientists did not support their discovery with any
archaeological evidence, Yang added.
</P>
<P>
Du Yongbin, a historian with the Chinese Center for Tibetan
Studies in Beijing, said all the historical documents on Tibet,
both in Tibetan and Chinese, do not ever mention pyramids at all.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000705.0299 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sea Level Rising Near Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Due to a side effect of its
breakneck pace of development, Shanghai is slowly sinking into the
sea, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
The relative sea level will rise 50-70 centimeters by 2050,
said Huang Runde, a senior engineer of the Shanghai Bureau of
Water Conservancy.
</P>
<P>
There are two factors contributing to rising sea level, one is
the global warming that melts the ice in polar areas, the other is
the sinking of the city caused by excessive use of groundwater, he
said.
</P>
<P>
"The city has been sinking at the speed of nearly ten
millimeters a year," said Zhang Xiangyu, director of the Shanghai
Water Supply Administration Office.
</P>
<P>
Zhang pointed out the exploitation of groundwater to support
the huge population, underground construction of subways and
basements below skyscrapers and overpasses has all led to ground
sinkage.
</P>
<P>
He said the city drafted laws on the annual drawing of
groundwater.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000705.0300 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Attorney General Slams "Old Power" For Tuesday Explosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian Attorney General Marzuki
Darusman slammed "old power" for Tuesday's bomb explosion in the
Attorney General's Office (AGO) which caused major damage to the
building's first floor.
</P>
<P>
"This is the work of the 'old power' who want to divert
attention from the real issue," Darusman was quoted by the
Indonesian Observer Wednesday as saying.
</P>
<P>
The blast came just an hour after prosecutors questioned former
president Soeharto's youngest son Hutomo "Tommy" Mandala Putra in
connection with his father's alleged involvement in graft.
</P>
<P>
Darusman said the bomb blast is only a "replay" of a March
shooting at the parliament building, which also took place shortly
after lawmakers grilled Tommy.
</P>
<P>
In March this year, when legislators questioned Tommy at the
parliament building over the use of funds from the now-defunct
Clove Marketing and Buffer Stock Managing Agency, an unidentified
man opened fires at the House Commission V's room, smashing glass
windows of the path leading to the room.
</P>
<P>
State prosecutor Suryansyah said probe into Tommy would be
continued as planned.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that South Jakarta police are currently
investigating the explosion, the first such case in 30 years.
</P>
<P>
Within minutes of the blast, police had arrested a man
identified only as Benny, a driver employed by PT Bahana. The
police suspected Benny of being the culprit because when the
explosion happened he was near the scene of incident.
</P>
<P>
The explosion ruined the ground floor's bathroom, the glass
door next to it and the windows of the bathroom on the second and
third floors. It also shattered a part of the building's wall.
</P>
<P>
The explosion is believed to be a warning to both the AGO and
the Attorney General over the current probe into the former
president's suspected involvement in a multi-billion U.S. dollars
graft case carried out during his 32 years reign.
</P>
<P>
Soeharto has been facing corruption charges in his 32 years
rule of the country. He was declared as suspect early this year
and was put under house arrest by the AGO in May. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
