<HEADLINE> Forest Fires Raging in Croatia's Mountainous Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Massive forest fires occurred in
Adriatic mountainous areas in Croatia in the past two days, local
media reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Wild flares have engulfed some 100 hectares of bush and pines
in Sibinik area.
</P>
<P>
Professional firefighters were sent there to put out the fires.
Some occurred in thunder-laden areas, hampering anti-fire
operations.
</P>
<P>
High temperatures and dry weather are believed to be the main
causes for the fires. 
</P>
