<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Steps up Developing Mini Vehicles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, July 5 (Xinhua) -- China produced some 500,000 mini
vehicles in the first half of this year, accounting for 1/3 of the
total vehicle output.
</P>
<P>
Sources with auto industry said that Chinese-made mini vehicles
include cars, vans and trucks, with an exhaust capacity below one
liter.
</P>
<P>
There are five major companies engaged in producing mini
vehicles, most of them were sole military factories, but now are
converting their technologies into civilian programs.
</P>
<P>
Experts forecast that mini vehicles will have a rosy picture in
the country, where many families are planning to buy comfortable
and cheap cars within several years.
</P>
<P>
The expansion of mini vehicle production will be a general
trend in China, according to Liu Tao, general manager of the Auto
Company of the Harbin Airplane Corporation, China's main mini
vehicle producer.
</P>
<P>
Besides mini vehicles, China produces 10 million motorcycles
every year. Experts believe that mini vehicle and motorcycle
industries will continue to be main fields attracting foreign
investment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
