<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Weeds Rampant in Taihu Lake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A greenish black belt of the weed in the Lake is 50 meters wide
and dozens of kilometers long, giving a repugent smell.
</P>
<P>
Experts said the rampant growth of blue algas is directly due
to the supernutrition of water caused by excessive discharge of
nitrogen, phosphor and others into the lake.
</P>
<P>
Water quality in the lake has notably worsened over the past
year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
