<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Offers "Weather Tour" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai residents, students in
particular, have more chances to know the secrets of weather
changes as they now can tour meteorological centers and radar
bases.
</P>
<P>
A meteorological science travel agency, the first in China,
will help them to find these excitements.
</P>
<P>
During a one-day "weather tour" organized by the agency, which
was set up here recently, people will follow meteorologists-turned
tour guides to enter a weather forecast studio to act as a
weatherman.
</P>
<P>
They can know the weather conditions of the day when he or she
was born by consulting computer databank.
</P>
<P>
The visitors can also roughly make simple weather forecast
themselves by combining weather factors including temperature, air
pressure and humidity.
</P>
<P>
In addition, they can also experience cyclones by watching
movies.
</P>
<P>
The travel agency is contacting more observatories, seismic
stations and experimental outer space centers so that travelers
would have more places to visit.
</P>
<P>
Vice-mayor of Shanghai Feng Guoqin said that such tour is a
good form of spreading weather knowledge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
