<BODY>
<HEADLINE> TV Series on China's No.1 Criminal Case Shooted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, July 5 (Xinhua) -- A 25-segment TV play series on China
's No.1 criminal case in 1997 is being shooted in Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region, northwest China.
</P>
<P>
The TV series tells about the crimes committed by Bai Baoshan,
who plundered three guns, shot dead 15 innocent persons, and
robbed more than 1.4 million yuan (186,674 U.S. dollars) in
Beijing, Hebei Province and Xinjiang within two years starting
from March, 1996.
</P>
<P>
The Interpol listed Bai's case the world's No.3 key criminal
case in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The TV series, to be shooted in Xinjiang and Beijing, will be
completed within three months.  
</P>
</TEXT>
