<HEADLINE> Hingis Defeated, Williams Sisters Make Semis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Top women's seed Martina Hingis was
crashed in the quarter-finals as the Williams sisters made the
semi-finals at the Wimbledon tennis championships on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Hingis lost to Venus Williams 6-3, 4-6, 4-6 in a fantastic
match at the center court. Venus will meet her younger sister
Serena Williams in the semi-final.
</P>
<P>
Serena crushed fellow American Lisa Raymond 6-2, 6-0 in a
comfortable quarter-final match.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time either sister has reached the last four at
the All England Club tournament.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Lindsay Davenport booked a meeting with
unseeded Australian Jelena Dokic, conqueror of Hingis in the first
round last year, after fellow American Monica Seles ran out of
steam in a 6-7 (7-4), 6-4, 6-0 defeat.
</P>
<P>
"I'm so happy to get through and I'm really happy about how I
hung in there," said Davenport after she recovered from a
tentative start to overwhelm Seles, who has never won Wimbledon,
in the final set.
</P>
<P>
Dokic had followed Serena Williams on to Court One, scene of
her stunning 1999 win over Hingis, and was almost as ruthless as
the American in defeating Magui Serna of Spain 6-3, 6-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
