<HEADLINE> Everton Seal Watson Signing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 4 (Xinhua) -- English premier league soccer club
Everton have confirmed the signing of Steve Watson from Aston
Villa for 2.5 million pounds.
</P>
<P>
The 26-year-old came through Monday's medical and has agreed
personal terms with the Blues, putting pen to paper on a five-year
deal.
</P>
<P>
Watson was delighted with the move and he said: "I can say
without a doubt this is a top six club and I just think the only
way is up for Everton due to the management we have got."
</P>
<P>
Everton boss Walter Smith was equally delighted and he said: "
We're pleased that Steve has decided to join us.
</P>
<P>
"I think we have had problems settling with our full-back
positions over the past two seasons, and hopefully Steve can help
us out in that department," he said.
</P>
<P>
England B international Watson is Smith's second signing of the
summer following Friday's capture of Alessandro Pistone from
Newcastle and it takes his spending to 5.5 million pounds.
</P>
</TEXT>
