<HEADLINE> U.S. Takes Beach Volleyball Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The American duo of Misty May
and Holly McPeak grabbed their first international gold medal
Tuesday by upsetting top-seeded Brazilians Adriana Behar and
Shelda Bede at the Chicago Grand Slam beach volleyball tournament.
</P>
<P>
The second-seeded U.S. team won 15-12 in a 50-minute match. It
was their first win over the Behar and Bede in their last five
matchups. The winners will split the 32,000 US dollars first-place
prize.
</P>
<P>
The two nations also faced off in the bronze medal match, where
Brazilians Sandra Pires and Adriana Samuel defeated the United
States' Linda Hanley and Nancy Reno 15-5 in a 43 minute match.
</P>
</TEXT>
