<HEADLINE> OSCE Parliamentary Assembly Session to Start in Bucharest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The session will gather 200 parliamentarians from 55 OSCE
member countries, among which OSCE Chairman-in-Office and Austrian
Foreign Minister Benita Ferreo-Waldner, Parliamentary Assembly
Secretary-General Spencer Oliver, OSCE Parliamentary Assembly
Deputy Secretary-General Vitaly Euseyeu and the members of the
Romanian Parliament delegation to the OSCE Parliamentary Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of the Council of Europe Parliamentary Assembly,
the Northern Council and the Black Sea Economic Cooperation will
also participate in the event.
</P>
<P>
OSCE Parliamentary Assembly chairman Helle Degn will open the
four-day works of the session. Romanian President Emil
Constantinescu, Senate chairman Ion Diaconescu, Chamber of
Deputies chairman Mircea Ionescu Quintus and Foreign Minister
Petre Roman will also speak in the opening.
</P>
<P>
The OSCE Parliamentary Assembly was set up in 1990 at the
summit in Paris to promote the organization's parliamentary
dimension.
</P>
<P>
The Assembly's main objective is to facilitate
interparliamentary dialogue and the annual session is its most
important activity.
</P>
<P>
The previous session took place in 1999 in Sankt Petersburg and
the future one will take in Paris in 2001.
</P>
<P>
At the latest OSCE summit in Istanbul over November 18-19, 1999,
Romania was designated to take over the presidency in 2001.
</P>
<P>
According to this decision, Romania is now part of the OSCE
troika along with Norway and Austria. 
</P>
</TEXT>
