SANTIAGO, July 5 (Xinhua) -- October is the deadline for Chile'
s Air Force (FACH) to present to the U.S. National Aeronautics and
Space Administration (NASA) its pilot,  Defense Minister Mario
Fernandez said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Fernandez said at a press conference that the Chilean
representative to NASA will be an official that has been prepared
in the United States, who will take part in scientific experiments
in the medical technological field.
</P>
<P>
The Chilean pilot will become after his preparation the first
South American astronaut to be able to go to the Moon and take
part in scientific projects, said the Defense minister.
</P>
<P>
Fernandez said that the Chilean government has great interest
in the completion of this project before the aforementioned
deadline.  
</P>
</TEXT>
